title.narrative: Strengthened capacity at central and municipal levels for scaling up of Home visiting scheme as a part of the decentralized family medicine systems for provision of quality maternal health, and child health and wellbeing services, particularly for the most vulnerable children including Kosovo Serbs in collaboration with education and child protection sectors

description.narrative: In total 256 service providers have been equipped with knowledge and skills to support parents on nurturing care and delivery of integrated and quality services including immunization, nutrition, responsive caregiving and early detection. A multisectoral working group has been established and is in the process of developing child feeding menus and guidelines. Four community based ECD centres have been established to increase the demand for and coverage of pre-school education focusing on children from vulnerable communities and children with disabilities. This action will ultimately contribute to strengthen central and municipal capacity for scaling up of UPHV | Status:On-track | As-of Date:09/01/2020
